Basic CSS

Basic CSS: Change the Color of Text
<h2 style="color:red;">CatPhotoApp</h2>

<h5> Basic CSS: Use CSS Selectors to Style Elements </h5>
<style>
  h2 {color:blue;}
</style>

Basic CSS: Style Multiple Elements with a CSS Class
<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  }
</style>

<h2 class="red-text">CatPhotoApp</h2>

Basic CSS: Change the Font Size of an Element
<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  p {
    font-size: 16px;
  }
  }
</style>

Basic CSS: Set the Font Family of an Element
<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  }

  p {
    font-family: monospace;
  }
</style>

Basic CSS: Import a Google Font
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lobster" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">

<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: monospace;
  }

  h2{
    font-family:Lobster;
  }
</style>

Basic CSS: Specify How Fonts Should Degrade
<!--
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lobster" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"> -->
<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: Lobster, monospace;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: monospace;
  }
</style>

Basic CSS: Size Your Images
<style>
  .smaller-image {
    width: 100px;
  }
</style>

<main>
  <a href="#"><img class="smaller-image" src="https://bit.ly/fcc-relaxing-cat" alt="A cute orange cat lying on its back."></a>
</main>

Basic CSS: Add Borders Around Your Elements
<style>
  .thick-green-border {
    border-color: green;
    border-width: 10px;
    border-style: solid;
  }
</style>
<main>
  <a href="#"><img class="smaller-image thick-green-border" src="https://bit.ly/fcc-relaxing-cat" alt="A cute orange cat lying on its back."></a>
</main>

Basic CSS: Add Rounded Corners with border-radius
  .thick-green-border {
    border-color: green;
    border-width: 10px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-radius: 10px
    }

Basic CSS: Make Circular Images with a border-radius
  .thick-green-border {
    border-color: green;
    border-width: 10px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

Basic CSS: Give a Background Color to a div Element
<style>
  .silver-background {
    background-color: silver;
  }
</style>
  <div class="silver-background">
    <p>Things cats love:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>cat nip</li>
      <li>laser pointers</li>
      <li>lasagna</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Top 3 things cats hate:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>flea treatment</li>
      <li>thunder</li>
      <li>other cats</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

Basic CSS: Set the id of an Element
  <form id="cat-photo-form" action="/submit-cat-photo">
    <label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor" checked> Indoor</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Outdoor</label><br>
    <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality" checked> Loving</label>
    <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality"> Lazy</label>
    <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality"> Energetic</label><br>
    <input type="text" placeholder="cat photo URL" required>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
  </form>

Basic CSS: Use an id Attribute to Style an Element
<style>
  #cat-photo-form {
    background-color: green;
  }
</style>

